Note:
VERSION CONSTRAINT - Semantic Versioning 2.0.0 Primitive (Tier 1)

Implements the Semantic Versioning 2.0.0 specification (https://semver.org)
plus the constraint-expression sublanguage adopted by Cargo, npm, and
pyproject. Provides:

  Version record  ........ major . minor . patch [- prerelease] [+ build]
  VersionConstraint ADT .. Exact / Min / Max / Range / Caret / Tilde / Wildcard
  version_parse / version_compare / version_satisfies

Layout (Version record, 40 bytes):
  offset  0 : major        (8 bytes)
  offset  8 : minor        (8 bytes)
  offset 16 : patch        (8 bytes)
  offset 24 : prerelease   (8 bytes, String pointer or 0)
  offset 32 : build        (8 bytes, String pointer or 0)

Layout (VersionConstraint record, 56 bytes):
  offset  0 : kind         (8 bytes, see VC_* constants)
  offset  8 : lower        (8 bytes, Version pointer or 0)
  offset 16 : upper        (8 bytes, Version pointer or 0)
  offset 24 : lower_inclusive (8 bytes, 0 or 1)
  offset 32 : upper_inclusive (8 bytes, 0 or 1)
  offset 40 : original_text (8 bytes, String pointer or 0 - for diagnostics)
  offset 48 : wildcard_at  (8 bytes, 0=major, 1=minor, 2=patch, -1 = N/A)

References:
  - SemVer 2.0.0 .......................... https://semver.org
  - Cargo manifest format ................. https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/reference/manifest.html#the-version-field
  - npm semver grammar .................... https://github.com/npm/node-semver
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/string_builder.runa" as SB
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/char_core.runa" as Char

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Let VERSION_SIZE be 40
Let VC_SIZE be 56

Note: VersionConstraint kinds.
Let VC_EXACT be 1
Let VC_MIN be 2
Let VC_MAX be 3
Let VC_RANGE be 4
Let VC_CARET be 5
Let VC_TILDE be 6
Let VC_WILDCARD be 7
Let VC_ANY be 8

Note: ============================================================================
Note: VERSION CONSTRUCTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Construct a Version record from three numeric components and optional
prerelease and build metadata strings. SemVer 2.0.0 mandates non-negative
integers for major/minor/patch with no leading zeros. Prerelease and build
identifiers are stored as already-validated String pointers (0 for absent).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Validate each numeric component is non-negative. Allocate the 40-byte
record and populate fields. The caller retains ownership of any passed
prerelease / build strings.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1). Single 40-byte allocation.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Negative components are rejected with sentinel 0 (NULL pointer) so callers
cannot accidentally construct ill-formed versions.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "version_create" takes major as Integer, minor as Integer, patch as Integer, prerelease as Integer, build as Integer returns Integer:
    If major is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If minor is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If patch is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let v be proc allocate from Layout with VERSION_SIZE
    If v is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with v, 0, major
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with v, 8, minor
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with v, 16, patch
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with v, 24, prerelease
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with v, 32, build
    Return v
End Process

@Reasoning
Destroy a Version record and any owned subordinate string allocations.
Prerelease and build pointers are caller-owned by default; this routine
deallocates only the record itself. Pair with version_destroy_deep when
the caller has transferred ownership.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free the record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must not touch the pointer after destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "version_destroy" takes v as Integer returns Integer:
    If v is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with v
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Destroy a Version record AND free its owned prerelease and build strings.
Used by parsers that allocated the strings themselves and hold sole
ownership.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Conditionally free each non-null subordinate pointer before freeing the
record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1). Up to three deallocations.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Double-free protection is the caller's responsibility; this routine does
not nil-out the input pointer.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "version_destroy_deep" takes v as Integer returns Integer:
    If v is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pre be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 24
    If pre is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with pre
    End If
    Let bld be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 32
    If bld is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with bld
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with v
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: VERSION FIELD ACCESSORS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Expose individual SemVer numeric components without forcing callers to
know the record layout.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load the 8-byte field at the documented offset.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns -1 on null input to distinguish error from a legitimate 0 major.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "version_major" takes v as Integer returns Integer:
    If v is equal to 0:
        Return -1
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the minor component.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns -1 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "version_minor" takes v as Integer returns Integer:
    If v is equal to 0:
        Return -1
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 8
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the patch component.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 16.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns -1 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "version_patch" takes v as Integer returns Integer:
    If v is equal to 0:
        Return -1
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 16
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the prerelease identifier string pointer per SemVer 2.0.0 Section 9.
Returns 0 if no prerelease tag is present.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 24.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must not mutate the returned string in place.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "version_prerelease" takes v as Integer returns Integer:
    If v is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 24
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the build metadata string pointer per SemVer 2.0.0 Section 10.
Returns 0 if no build metadata is attached.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 32.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must not mutate the returned string in place.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "version_build" takes v as Integer returns Integer:
    If v is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 32
End Process

@Reasoning
True if the version carries a prerelease tag. Per SemVer 2.0.0 Section 9,
the presence of a prerelease tag makes the version "less than" the
equivalent release-version with the same numeric components.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Test prerelease pointer for non-null and nonzero string length. A
zero-length prerelease string is treated as absent.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No external input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "version_is_prerelease" takes v as Integer returns Integer:
    If v is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pre be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 24
    If pre is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let len be proc string_length from StringCore with pre
    If len is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: VERSION PARSE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Parse a SemVer 2.0.0 version string of the form
"MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH[-PRERELEASE][+BUILD]". The grammar follows the SemVer
2.0.0 specification literally:

  - MAJOR / MINOR / PATCH are non-negative integers without leading zeros
    (except the literal "0").
  - PRERELEASE is a series of dot-separated identifiers, each composed of
    ASCII alphanumeric characters and hyphens. Numeric identifiers must
    not have leading zeros.
  - BUILD is a series of dot-separated identifiers from the same alphabet,
    but numeric identifiers may carry leading zeros.

Returns 0 on any malformed input so callers never observe a partial
Version record.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Two-pass scanner. Pass one walks the string once to identify the
delimiters ('.', '-', '+'). Pass two extracts the four substrings, parses
the three numeric components with bounds checks, and copies the
prerelease and build identifier strings into freshly-allocated buffers.
SemVer disallows leading zeros on numeric components longer than one
character. Each numeric component is checked digit-by-digit before
calling string_to_integer so we can reject leading zeros explicitly.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over the input. Space: O(n) for the prerelease and build
copies plus the 40-byte record.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Strict validation prevents silent acceptance of pseudo-versions such as
"01.02.03" or "1.2" that some lax parsers tolerate. Per SemVer 2.0.0
Section 2, only well-formed inputs produce a non-null record.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "version_parse" takes text as Integer returns Integer:
    If text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with text
    If length is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Locate the three delimiters: first '.', second '.', then '-' / '+'.
    Let dot1 be -1
    Let dot2 be -1
    Let dash_pos be -1
    Let plus_pos be -1

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than length:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, i
        If ch is equal to 46:
            If dot1 is equal to -1:
                Set dot1 to i
            Otherwise:
                If dot2 is equal to -1:
                    If dash_pos is equal to -1:
                        If plus_pos is equal to -1:
                            Set dot2 to i
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        If ch is equal to 45:
            If dash_pos is equal to -1:
                If plus_pos is equal to -1:
                    Set dash_pos to i
                End If
            End If
        End If
        If ch is equal to 43:
            If plus_pos is equal to -1:
                Set plus_pos to i
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    If dot1 is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    If dot2 is less than (dot1 plus 2):
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Determine the end-of-patch boundary.
    Let patch_end be length
    If dash_pos is not equal to -1:
        Set patch_end to dash_pos
    Otherwise:
        If plus_pos is not equal to -1:
            Set patch_end to plus_pos
        End If
    End If
    If patch_end is less than (dot2 plus 2):
        Return 0
    End If

    Let major_str be proc string_substring from StringPrim with text, 0, dot1
    If major_str is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let minor_len be (dot2 minus dot1) minus 1
    Let minor_str be proc string_substring from StringPrim with text, (dot1 plus 1), minor_len
    If minor_str is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with major_str
        Return 0
    End If
    Let patch_len be (patch_end minus dot2) minus 1
    Let patch_str be proc string_substring from StringPrim with text, (dot2 plus 1), patch_len
    If patch_str is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with major_str
        proc deallocate from Layout with minor_str
        Return 0
    End If

    Let major_valid be proc validate_numeric_identifier with major_str
    Let minor_valid be proc validate_numeric_identifier with minor_str
    Let patch_valid be proc validate_numeric_identifier with patch_str

    If major_valid is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with major_str
        proc deallocate from Layout with minor_str
        proc deallocate from Layout with patch_str
        Return 0
    End If
    If minor_valid is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with major_str
        proc deallocate from Layout with minor_str
        proc deallocate from Layout with patch_str
        Return 0
    End If
    If patch_valid is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with major_str
        proc deallocate from Layout with minor_str
        proc deallocate from Layout with patch_str
        Return 0
    End If

    Let major_val be proc string_to_integer from StringPrim with major_str
    Let minor_val be proc string_to_integer from StringPrim with minor_str
    Let patch_val be proc string_to_integer from StringPrim with patch_str
    proc deallocate from Layout with major_str
    proc deallocate from Layout with minor_str
    proc deallocate from Layout with patch_str

    Note: Extract prerelease identifier substring (between '-' and '+', if any).
    Let pre_str be 0
    If dash_pos is not equal to -1:
        Let pre_start be dash_pos plus 1
        Let pre_end be length
        If plus_pos is not equal to -1:
            If plus_pos is greater than dash_pos:
                Set pre_end to plus_pos
            End If
        End If
        Let pre_len be pre_end minus pre_start
        If pre_len is less than 1:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set pre_str to proc string_substring from StringPrim with text, pre_start, pre_len
        If pre_str is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let pre_ok be proc validate_identifier_series with pre_str, 1
        If pre_ok is equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with pre_str
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    Let bld_str be 0
    If plus_pos is not equal to -1:
        Let bld_start be plus_pos plus 1
        Let bld_len be length minus bld_start
        If bld_len is less than 1:
            If pre_str is not equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with pre_str
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
        Set bld_str to proc string_substring from StringPrim with text, bld_start, bld_len
        If bld_str is equal to 0:
            If pre_str is not equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with pre_str
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
        Let bld_ok be proc validate_identifier_series with bld_str, 0
        If bld_ok is equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with bld_str
            If pre_str is not equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with pre_str
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    Let v be proc version_create with major_val, minor_val, patch_val, pre_str, bld_str
    If v is equal to 0:
        If pre_str is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with pre_str
        End If
        If bld_str is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with bld_str
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    Return v
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper: validate that a substring is a SemVer numeric identifier
(SemVer 2.0.0 Section 2). All characters must be ASCII digits. Multi-digit
strings must not begin with '0'. A zero-length identifier is invalid.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk the string. Reject non-digits, reject leading zero on multi-digit
inputs, accept everything else.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over the identifier. Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper. Does not allocate.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "validate_numeric_identifier" takes s as Integer returns Integer:
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with s
    If length is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    Let first_char be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with s, 0
    Let first_is_digit be proc is_digit from Char with first_char
    If first_is_digit is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If length is greater than 1:
        If first_char is equal to 48:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    While i is less than length:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with s, i
        Let ok be proc is_digit from Char with ch
        If ok is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper: validate a dot-separated series of SemVer identifiers (Section 9
for prerelease, Section 10 for build). Each identifier consists of ASCII
alphanumeric characters plus '-'. If strict_no_leading_zero is 1 we are
in prerelease mode and numeric identifiers must not have leading zeros.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk the string. Split on '.', validate each segment per the alphabet
rule plus the conditional leading-zero rule for numeric-only segments.
A trailing dot or empty segment is invalid.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over the input. Space: O(1) - operates in place.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper. Does not allocate.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "validate_identifier_series" takes s as Integer, strict_no_leading_zero as Integer returns Integer:
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with s
    If length is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let seg_start be 0
    Let i be 0
    Let result be 1
    While i is less than length:
        If result is equal to 0:
            Set i to length
        Otherwise:
            Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with s, i
            If ch is equal to 46:
                Let seg_len be i minus seg_start
                Let seg_ok be proc validate_single_identifier with s, seg_start, seg_len, strict_no_leading_zero
                If seg_ok is equal to 0:
                    Set result to 0
                End If
                Set seg_start to i plus 1
                Set i to i plus 1
            Otherwise:
                Set i to i plus 1
            End If
        End If
    End While
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tail_len be length minus seg_start
    Let tail_ok be proc validate_single_identifier with s, seg_start, tail_len, strict_no_leading_zero
    Return tail_ok
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper: validate one identifier inside the dot-separated series. Range
[start, start+len) within s. Alphabet: [0-9A-Za-z-]. Length must be > 0.
If the segment is entirely digits and strict_no_leading_zero is 1, the
leading-zero rule applies (multi-digit must not begin with '0').
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
First scan: enforce alphabet and capture all_digits flag. Second test:
apply leading-zero rule if the segment is fully numeric.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(len). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "validate_single_identifier" takes s as Integer, start as Integer, length as Integer, strict_no_leading_zero as Integer returns Integer:
    If length is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let all_digits be 1
    Let j be 0
    While j is less than length:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with s, start plus j
        Let is_d be proc is_digit from Char with ch
        Let is_a be proc is_alpha from Char with ch
        If is_d is equal to 0:
            Set all_digits to 0
            If is_a is equal to 0:
                If ch is not equal to 45:
                    Return 0
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set j to j plus 1
    End While
    If all_digits is equal to 1:
        If strict_no_leading_zero is equal to 1:
            If length is greater than 1:
                Let first_ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with s, start
                If first_ch is equal to 48:
                    Return 0
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: VERSION FORMAT
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Render a Version record as a SemVer-conformant canonical string. Output
matches the parser grammar exactly so round-tripping parse + format is
the identity on valid inputs.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
StringBuilder-assemble "MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH" then append "-PRERELEASE" and
"+BUILD" if those fields are non-null.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) where n is the rendered length. Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No external input is interpreted. Caller owns the returned string.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "version_to_string" takes v as Integer returns Integer:
    If v is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let major be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 0
    Let minor be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 8
    Let patch be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 16
    Let pre be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 24
    Let bld be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 32

    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc stringbuilder_append_integer from SB with sb, major
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 46
    proc stringbuilder_append_integer from SB with sb, minor
    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 46
    proc stringbuilder_append_integer from SB with sb, patch
    If pre is not equal to 0:
        Let pre_len be proc string_length from StringCore with pre
        If pre_len is greater than 0:
            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 45
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, pre
        End If
    End If
    If bld is not equal to 0:
        Let bld_len be proc string_length from StringCore with bld
        If bld_len is greater than 0:
            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 43
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, bld
        End If
    End If
    Let result be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: VERSION COMPARISON
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Three-way compare two Version records per SemVer 2.0.0 Section 11:
  1. Numeric major / minor / patch in lexicographic order.
  2. A version without prerelease tag is greater than one with the same
     numeric components and a prerelease tag.
  3. Prerelease identifiers are compared by:
       a) dot-separated identifiers,
       b) within each identifier: numeric < alphanumeric,
       c) numeric identifiers by numeric value,
       d) alphanumeric identifiers by ASCII order,
       e) shorter identifier list with all leading identifiers equal
          ranks lower.
  4. Build metadata is IGNORED for ordering (Section 10).

Returns -1 / 0 / 1.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Compare numeric triples first. Then check both prerelease flags. If
exactly one has a prerelease the one with it is less. If both do, walk
their dot-separated identifier sequences applying the alphabet-aware
rule.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(p) where p is the combined prerelease identifier length. Space:
O(p) for the segment scratch (per-segment substring allocations).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Inputs are not externally controlled at this layer; the parser has
already enforced format. No state is mutated.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "version_compare" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is equal to 0:
        If b is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return -1
    End If
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let a_major be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a, 0
    Let b_major be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with b, 0
    If a_major is less than b_major:
        Return -1
    End If
    If a_major is greater than b_major:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let a_minor be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a, 8
    Let b_minor be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with b, 8
    If a_minor is less than b_minor:
        Return -1
    End If
    If a_minor is greater than b_minor:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let a_patch be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a, 16
    Let b_patch be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with b, 16
    If a_patch is less than b_patch:
        Return -1
    End If
    If a_patch is greater than b_patch:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let a_pre be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a, 24
    Let b_pre be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with b, 24
    Let a_has_pre be 0
    If a_pre is not equal to 0:
        Let al be proc string_length from StringCore with a_pre
        If al is greater than 0:
            Set a_has_pre to 1
        End If
    End If
    Let b_has_pre be 0
    If b_pre is not equal to 0:
        Let bl be proc string_length from StringCore with b_pre
        If bl is greater than 0:
            Set b_has_pre to 1
        End If
    End If
    If a_has_pre is equal to 0:
        If b_has_pre is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return 1
    End If
    If b_has_pre is equal to 0:
        Return -1
    End If
    Return proc compare_prerelease with a_pre, b_pre
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper: compare two prerelease strings per SemVer 2.0.0 Section 11 (4):
walk dot-separated identifiers; numeric identifiers compare numerically
and rank below alphanumerics; when one identifier list runs out before
the other and all preceding identifiers are equal, the shorter list ranks
lower.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Two cursors walk both strings simultaneously. For each segment we
allocate substrings, classify (all-digit vs mixed), and apply the rule.
Allocations are released as we go to bound resident memory.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(p) over the combined identifier length. Space: O(p) for
per-segment scratch substrings (released eagerly).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Inputs already validated by the parser.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "compare_prerelease" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Let a_len be proc string_length from StringCore with a
    Let b_len be proc string_length from StringCore with b
    Let ai be 0
    Let bi be 0
    Let result be 0
    Let done be 0
    While done is equal to 0:
        If ai is greater than or equal to a_len:
            If bi is greater than or equal to b_len:
                Set done to 1
            Otherwise:
                Set result to -1
                Set done to 1
            End If
        Otherwise:
            If bi is greater than or equal to b_len:
                Set result to 1
                Set done to 1
            Otherwise:
                Let a_seg_end be ai
                Let a_break be 0
                While a_break is equal to 0:
                    If a_seg_end is greater than or equal to a_len:
                        Set a_break to 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Let ach be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with a, a_seg_end
                        If ach is equal to 46:
                            Set a_break to 1
                        Otherwise:
                            Set a_seg_end to a_seg_end plus 1
                        End If
                    End If
                End While
                Let b_seg_end be bi
                Let b_break be 0
                While b_break is equal to 0:
                    If b_seg_end is greater than or equal to b_len:
                        Set b_break to 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Let bch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with b, b_seg_end
                        If bch is equal to 46:
                            Set b_break to 1
                        Otherwise:
                            Set b_seg_end to b_seg_end plus 1
                        End If
                    End If
                End While
                Let a_seg_len be a_seg_end minus ai
                Let b_seg_len be b_seg_end minus bi
                Let a_seg be proc string_substring from StringPrim with a, ai, a_seg_len
                Let b_seg be proc string_substring from StringPrim with b, bi, b_seg_len
                Let cmp be proc compare_one_identifier with a_seg, b_seg
                If a_seg is not equal to 0:
                    proc deallocate from Layout with a_seg
                End If
                If b_seg is not equal to 0:
                    proc deallocate from Layout with b_seg
                End If
                If cmp is not equal to 0:
                    Set result to cmp
                    Set done to 1
                Otherwise:
                    Set ai to a_seg_end plus 1
                    Set bi to b_seg_end plus 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper: compare a single prerelease identifier pair. Numeric ranks below
alphanumeric; numerics compare by value; alphanumerics by ASCII order.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Classify both via all-digit scan. If one is numeric and the other is
not, numeric < alphanumeric. If both numeric, parse to integers and
compare. Otherwise, byte-wise lexicographic compare.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(len). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Inputs validated upstream.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "compare_one_identifier" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is equal to 0:
        If b is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return -1
    End If
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let a_digit be proc identifier_is_numeric with a
    Let b_digit be proc identifier_is_numeric with b
    If a_digit is equal to 1:
        If b_digit is equal to 0:
            Return -1
        End If
        Let av be proc string_to_integer from StringPrim with a
        Let bv be proc string_to_integer from StringPrim with b
        If av is less than bv:
            Return -1
        End If
        If av is greater than bv:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    If b_digit is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return proc string_compare from StringCore with a, b
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper: returns 1 if a string is fully composed of ASCII digits, else 0.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Linear scan checking each byte against is_digit.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(len). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "identifier_is_numeric" takes s as Integer returns Integer:
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with s
    If length is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than length:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with s, i
        Let d be proc is_digit from Char with ch
        If d is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTRAINT CONSTRUCTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate a VersionConstraint record with the supplied kind discriminator
and bounds. The lower/upper Version pointers are caller-owned references
(the constraint does not deep-copy). Inclusive flags are 0 or 1.
wildcard_at is meaningful only for VC_WILDCARD; pass -1 otherwise.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 56 bytes and populate fields per the layout comment.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller is responsible for the validity of the supplied Version pointers.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "constraint_create" takes kind as Integer, lower as Integer, upper as Integer, lower_inclusive as Integer, upper_inclusive as Integer, original_text as Integer, wildcard_at as Integer returns Integer:
    If kind is less than VC_EXACT:
        Return 0
    End If
    If kind is greater than VC_ANY:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let c be proc allocate from Layout with VC_SIZE
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 0, kind
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 8, lower
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 16, upper
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 24, lower_inclusive
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 32, upper_inclusive
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 40, original_text
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with c, 48, wildcard_at
    Return c
End Process

@Reasoning
Destroy a constraint record. By contract the Version bounds are caller-
owned and not freed here. Pair with constraint_destroy_deep to release
the bounds as well.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free the record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must not touch the pointer after destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "constraint_destroy" takes c as Integer returns Integer:
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with c
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Destroy a constraint AND its bound Versions plus its original-text
string. Used by parsers that own the bounds outright.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free each non-null subordinate before freeing the record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Double-free protection is the caller's responsibility.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "constraint_destroy_deep" takes c as Integer returns Integer:
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let lo be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, 8
    If lo is not equal to 0:
        proc version_destroy_deep with lo
    End If
    Let hi be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, 16
    If hi is not equal to 0:
        proc version_destroy_deep with hi
    End If
    Let txt be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, 40
    If txt is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with txt
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with c
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTRAINT PARSE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Parse a constraint expression as accepted by Cargo and npm:
  - "1.2.3"  ............ exact match
  - "^1.2.3" ............ caret: compatible up to next major
  - "~1.2.3" ............ tilde: compatible up to next minor
  - ">=1.2.3" ........... minimum (inclusive)
  - ">1.2.3" ............ minimum (exclusive)
  - "<=1.2.3" ........... maximum (inclusive)
  - "<1.2.3" ............ maximum (exclusive)
  - "1.2.*" / "1.*" ..... wildcard
  - "*" ................. any version
  - ">=1.0.0 <2.0.0" .... range (lower inclusive, upper exclusive)
A wildcard inside a range is not accepted - the parser rejects mixed
forms because the union semantics differ across ecosystems.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Trim leading inline whitespace. Dispatch on first character:
  '*'  -> VC_ANY
  '^'  -> VC_CARET
  '~'  -> VC_TILDE
  '>'  -> VC_MIN (with optional '=' suffix)
  '<'  -> VC_MAX (with optional '=' suffix)
  '='  -> VC_EXACT
  digit -> VC_EXACT, unless the version body contains '*' -> VC_WILDCARD
After the operator we delegate the version body to version_parse_relaxed
which permits the wildcard tail. For two-clause ranges we look for an
inline-whitespace boundary and parse both halves.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over input. Space: O(n) for the original-text copy and the
Version sub-records.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Strict: any malformed sub-expression aborts the parse with sentinel 0
so the caller never gets a partially-initialized constraint.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "constraint_parse" takes text as Integer returns Integer:
    If text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let raw_len be proc string_length from StringCore with text
    If raw_len is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let start be 0
    Let trim_done be 0
    While trim_done is equal to 0:
        If start is greater than or equal to raw_len:
            Set trim_done to 1
        Otherwise:
            Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, start
            Let ws be proc is_inline_whitespace from Char with ch
            If ws is equal to 1:
                Set start to start plus 1
            Otherwise:
                Set trim_done to 1
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Note: Find an inline-whitespace boundary for two-clause ranges.
    Let split_pos be -1
    Let i be start
    While i is less than raw_len:
        Let ch2 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, i
        Let ws2 be proc is_inline_whitespace from Char with ch2
        If ws2 is equal to 1:
            Set split_pos to i
            Set i to raw_len
        Otherwise:
            Set i to i plus 1
        End If
    End While

    Let original be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with text
    If original is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If split_pos is greater than 0:
        Note: Two-clause range.
        Let left_len be split_pos minus start
        Let left_text be proc string_substring from StringPrim with text, start, left_len
        If left_text is equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with original
            Return 0
        End If
        Let right_start be split_pos plus 1
        Let rtrim_done be 0
        While rtrim_done is equal to 0:
            If right_start is greater than or equal to raw_len:
                Set rtrim_done to 1
            Otherwise:
                Let rch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, right_start
                Let rws be proc is_inline_whitespace from Char with rch
                If rws is equal to 1:
                    Set right_start to right_start plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    Set rtrim_done to 1
                End If
            End If
        End While
        Let right_len be raw_len minus right_start
        Let right_text be proc string_substring from StringPrim with text, right_start, right_len
        If right_text is equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with original
            proc deallocate from Layout with left_text
            Return 0
        End If

        Let lower_pair be proc parse_comparator with left_text
        Let upper_pair be proc parse_comparator with right_text
        proc deallocate from Layout with left_text
        proc deallocate from Layout with right_text
        If lower_pair is equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with original
            Return 0
        End If
        If upper_pair is equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with original
            Let lv be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lower_pair, 0
            If lv is not equal to 0:
                proc version_destroy_deep with lv
            End If
            proc deallocate from Layout with lower_pair
            Return 0
        End If

        Let lv be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lower_pair, 0
        Let lk be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lower_pair, 8
        Let li be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lower_pair, 16
        Let uv be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with upper_pair, 0
        Let uk be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with upper_pair, 8
        Let ui be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with upper_pair, 16
        proc deallocate from Layout with lower_pair
        proc deallocate from Layout with upper_pair

        If lk is not equal to VC_MIN:
            proc deallocate from Layout with original
            If lv is not equal to 0:
                proc version_destroy_deep with lv
            End If
            If uv is not equal to 0:
                proc version_destroy_deep with uv
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
        If uk is not equal to VC_MAX:
            proc deallocate from Layout with original
            If lv is not equal to 0:
                proc version_destroy_deep with lv
            End If
            If uv is not equal to 0:
                proc version_destroy_deep with uv
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
        Return proc constraint_create with VC_RANGE, lv, uv, li, ui, original, -1
    End If

    Note: Single comparator.
    Let body_len be raw_len minus start
    Let body be proc string_substring from StringPrim with text, start, body_len
    If body is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with original
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pair be proc parse_comparator with body
    proc deallocate from Layout with body
    If pair is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with original
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pv be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with pair, 0
    Let pk be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with pair, 8
    Let pi be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with pair, 16
    Let pw be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with pair, 24
    proc deallocate from Layout with pair

    If pk is equal to VC_ANY:
        Return proc constraint_create with VC_ANY, 0, 0, 0, 0, original, -1
    End If
    If pk is equal to VC_WILDCARD:
        Return proc constraint_create with VC_WILDCARD, pv, 0, 1, 0, original, pw
    End If
    If pk is equal to VC_EXACT:
        Return proc constraint_create with VC_EXACT, pv, pv, 1, 1, original, -1
    End If
    If pk is equal to VC_MIN:
        Return proc constraint_create with VC_MIN, pv, 0, pi, 0, original, -1
    End If
    If pk is equal to VC_MAX:
        Return proc constraint_create with VC_MAX, 0, pv, 0, pi, original, -1
    End If
    If pk is equal to VC_CARET:
        Return proc constraint_create with VC_CARET, pv, 0, 1, 0, original, -1
    End If
    If pk is equal to VC_TILDE:
        Return proc constraint_create with VC_TILDE, pv, 0, 1, 0, original, -1
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with original
    If pv is not equal to 0:
        proc version_destroy_deep with pv
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper: parse a single comparator expression. Returns a 32-byte transit
record (later freed by the caller) carrying:
  offset 0  : Version pointer (owned)
  offset 8  : kind discriminator
  offset 16 : inclusive flag
  offset 24 : wildcard_at (-1 if not a wildcard)
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Dispatch on the first character of the trimmed comparator string,
extract the version body, and delegate to version_parse or
version_parse_with_wildcards depending on whether '*' appears.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n) for the version body substring and the 32-byte
transit record.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper. Returns 0 on any malformed input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "parse_comparator" takes text as Integer returns Integer:
    If text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with text
    If length is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let first be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, 0
    If first is equal to 42:
        Let pair be proc allocate from Layout with 32
        If pair is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pair, 0, 0
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pair, 8, VC_ANY
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pair, 16, 0
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pair, 24, -1
        Return pair
    End If

    Let op_kind be VC_EXACT
    Let inclusive be 1
    Let body_start be 0
    If first is equal to 94:
        Set op_kind to VC_CARET
        Set body_start to 1
    Otherwise:
        If first is equal to 126:
            Set op_kind to VC_TILDE
            Set body_start to 1
        Otherwise:
            If first is equal to 61:
                Set op_kind to VC_EXACT
                Set body_start to 1
            Otherwise:
                If first is equal to 62:
                    Set op_kind to VC_MIN
                    Set body_start to 1
                    If length is greater than 1:
                        Let second be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, 1
                        If second is equal to 61:
                            Set inclusive to 1
                            Set body_start to 2
                        Otherwise:
                            Set inclusive to 0
                        End If
                    End If
                Otherwise:
                    If first is equal to 60:
                        Set op_kind to VC_MAX
                        Set body_start to 1
                        If length is greater than 1:
                            Let second2 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, 1
                            If second2 is equal to 61:
                                Set inclusive to 1
                                Set body_start to 2
                            Otherwise:
                                Set inclusive to 0
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let body_len be length minus body_start
    If body_len is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let body be proc string_substring from StringPrim with text, body_start, body_len
    If body is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let star_pos be -1
    Let k be 0
    While k is less than body_len:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with body, k
        If ch is equal to 42:
            Set star_pos to k
            Set k to body_len
        Otherwise:
            Set k to k plus 1
        End If
    End While

    Let v be 0
    Let w_at be -1
    If star_pos is equal to -1:
        Set v to proc version_parse with body
        If v is equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with body
            Return 0
        End If
    Otherwise:
        If op_kind is not equal to VC_EXACT:
            proc deallocate from Layout with body
            Return 0
        End If
        Set op_kind to VC_WILDCARD
        Let wpair be proc parse_wildcard_version with body
        proc deallocate from Layout with body
        If wpair is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set v to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with wpair, 0
        Set w_at to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with wpair, 8
        proc deallocate from Layout with wpair
        Let pair2 be proc allocate from Layout with 32
        If pair2 is equal to 0:
            proc version_destroy_deep with v
            Return 0
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pair2, 0, v
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pair2, 8, op_kind
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pair2, 16, inclusive
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pair2, 24, w_at
        Return pair2
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with body

    Let pair be proc allocate from Layout with 32
    If pair is equal to 0:
        proc version_destroy_deep with v
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pair, 0, v
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pair, 8, op_kind
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pair, 16, inclusive
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pair, 24, w_at
    Return pair
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper: parse a wildcard version body of the form "MAJOR.*", "MAJOR.MINOR.*",
or "*". Returns a 16-byte transit record with the canonical Version
substituted for the '*' position and the wildcard_at index (0=major,
1=minor, 2=patch). The substituted Version uses 0 for the wildcarded
component and any below it, matching Cargo / npm conventions.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk the components. The '*' must appear in exactly one slot and may not
co-occur with prerelease or build segments. The companion non-wildcard
slots must satisfy the numeric-identifier rule.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n) for the substituted Version record plus the
16-byte transit record.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper. Returns 0 on any malformed input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "parse_wildcard_version" takes body as Integer returns Integer:
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with body
    If length is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let first be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with body, 0
    If length is equal to 1:
        If first is equal to 42:
            Let v_any be proc version_create with 0, 0, 0, 0, 0
            If v_any is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            Let pair be proc allocate from Layout with 16
            If pair is equal to 0:
                proc version_destroy_deep with v_any
                Return 0
            End If
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pair, 0, v_any
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pair, 8, 0
            Return pair
        End If
        Return 0
    End If

    Let dot1 be -1
    Let dot2 be -1
    Let star_pos be -1
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than length:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with body, i
        If ch is equal to 46:
            If dot1 is equal to -1:
                Set dot1 to i
            Otherwise:
                If dot2 is equal to -1:
                    Set dot2 to i
                End If
            End If
        End If
        If ch is equal to 42:
            Set star_pos to i
        End If
        If ch is equal to 45:
            Return 0
        End If
        If ch is equal to 43:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    If star_pos is equal to -1:
        Return 0
    End If
    If star_pos is not equal to (length minus 1):
        Return 0
    End If
    If star_pos is greater than 0:
        Let prev be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with body, star_pos minus 1
        If prev is not equal to 46:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    Let w_at be 0
    Let major_val be 0
    Let minor_val be 0
    Let patch_val be 0
    If dot1 is equal to -1:
        Set w_at to 0
    Otherwise:
        Let major_str be proc string_substring from StringPrim with body, 0, dot1
        Let mv_ok be proc validate_numeric_identifier with major_str
        If mv_ok is equal to 0:
            If major_str is not equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with major_str
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
        Set major_val to proc string_to_integer from StringPrim with major_str
        proc deallocate from Layout with major_str
        If dot2 is equal to -1:
            Note: pattern "MAJOR.*"
            Set w_at to 1
        Otherwise:
            Let minor_len be (dot2 minus dot1) minus 1
            Let minor_str be proc string_substring from StringPrim with body, dot1 plus 1, minor_len
            Let mvok be proc validate_numeric_identifier with minor_str
            If mvok is equal to 0:
                If minor_str is not equal to 0:
                    proc deallocate from Layout with minor_str
                End If
                Return 0
            End If
            Set minor_val to proc string_to_integer from StringPrim with minor_str
            proc deallocate from Layout with minor_str
            Set w_at to 2
        End If
    End If

    Let v be proc version_create with major_val, minor_val, patch_val, 0, 0
    If v is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pair be proc allocate from Layout with 16
    If pair is equal to 0:
        proc version_destroy_deep with v
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pair, 0, v
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with pair, 8, w_at
    Return pair
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTRAINT FIELD ACCESSORS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Expose the discriminator kind for switch-style dispatch by callers
without exposing the layout.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input - distinct from VC_EXACT (which is 1) so
callers can detect error.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "constraint_kind" takes c as Integer returns Integer:
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the lower-bound Version pointer.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 if absent or input is null.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "constraint_lower" takes c as Integer returns Integer:
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with c, 8
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the upper-bound Version pointer.
@End Reasoning

